It's a perfect number.

1088
01:01:28,810 --> 01:01:29,768
- Awesome!

1089
01:01:29,894 --> 01:01:31,311
- Where did you get that?

1090
01:01:31,437 --> 01:01:32,771
- I made it.

1091
01:01:32,897 --> 01:01:35,607
42 plus 5 equals 48.

1092
01:01:35,733 --> 01:01:38,568
- No, it's not.
It's 47.

1093
01:01:40,196 --> 01:01:42,072
- You didn't make it.

1094
01:01:42,198 --> 01:01:44,783
I know who it belongs to.

1095
01:01:44,909 --> 01:01:47,119
- It's mine, and I made it.

1096
01:01:48,413 --> 01:01:51,415
[Bell ringing]

1097
01:01:54,961 --> 01:01:57,587
[Children chattering]

1098
01:01:57,714 --> 01:01:59,089
- Go on, Lisa.

1099
01:01:59,215 --> 01:02:02,718
- Okay, but don't let her
get away with anything.

1100
01:02:06,723 --> 01:02:11,768
- So how about you and I go
to the hardware store together

1101
01:02:11,894 --> 01:02:15,939
and we'll give the number back
to Mr. Jones?

1102
01:02:16,065 --> 01:02:19,776
I mean, he'll be so happy
that he got his number back,

1103
01:02:19,902 --> 01:02:21,486
he may even give you a reward.

1104
01:02:21,612 --> 01:02:23,447
- A reward?

1105
01:02:23,573 --> 01:02:26,116
I don't want a stupid reward.

1106
01:02:26,242 --> 01:02:28,702
And you cannot keep me
from recess.

1107
01:02:28,828 --> 01:02:31,997
- Give... it... to me.

1108
01:02:40,923 --> 01:02:42,924
- Weirdo.

1109
01:02:49,265 --> 01:02:50,307
- I'll go.

1110
01:02:53,352 --> 01:02:56,229
I'll go to the hardware store
with you.

1111
01:02:56,355 --> 01:02:59,775
Then you can take me
to visit my mom.

1112
01:03:03,529 --> 01:03:05,030
- Hey, you psyched

1113
01:03:05,156 --> 01:03:07,032
for the sulfuric acid experiment
tomorrow?

1114
01:03:07,158 --> 01:03:08,825
We're gonna rock that.

1115
01:03:12,371 --> 01:03:13,955
- Mr. Smith.

1116
01:03:14,081 --> 01:03:15,832
- What's up?

1117
01:03:15,958 --> 01:03:17,667
- Want to come
to the hardware store

1118
01:03:17,794 --> 01:03:19,044
with me and Miss Gray?

1119
01:03:19,170 --> 01:03:20,253
- I can't.

1120
01:03:20,379 --> 01:03:22,047
I have my after-school
science club meeting.

1121
01:03:22,173 --> 01:03:24,716
I have to show up
because I said I would,

1122
01:03:24,842 --> 01:03:27,010
and I always mean what I say
and say what I mean.

1123
01:03:27,136 --> 01:03:28,303
I'm a straight shooter.

1124
01:03:28,429 --> 01:03:29,971
Not everyone is, but...

1125
01:03:30,097 --> 01:03:31,848
Hey, listen,
thanks for the invite.

1126
01:03:31,974 --> 01:03:35,060
- You're gonna miss a good time.

1127
01:03:39,273 --> 01:03:44,986
- Mr. Jones?

1128
01:03:51,577 --> 01:03:53,495
Mr. Jones?

1129
01:03:56,624 --> 01:03:59,376
If he's not here, why would he
leave his door open?

1130
01:03:59,502 --> 01:04:02,546
- Maybe he was captured
by pirates.

1131
01:04:14,892 --> 01:04:16,309
This way.

1132
01:04:20,356 --> 01:04:22,691
- "And falling on a bench,
he laughed until the tears..."

1133
01:04:22,817 --> 01:04:24,234
- Mom!
Nan!

1134
01:04:24,360 --> 01:04:25,694
- Hi.

1135
01:04:33,703 --> 01:04:38,373
- This is my math teacher,
Miss Gray.

1136
01:04:38,499 --> 01:04:41,877
- Is she an invisible
math teacher?

1137
01:04:42,920 --> 01:04:44,379
- Miss Gray?

1138
01:04:49,594 --> 01:04:53,722
This is Miss Gray.

1139
01:04:54,974 --> 01:04:56,558
- Lisa, you want to get
some potato chips?

1140
01:04:56,684 --> 01:04:57,726
- Aye-aye, matey.

1141
01:04:57,852 --> 01:04:58,977
- Arr!
Shiver me timbers.

1142
01:04:59,103 --> 01:05:00,020
Well, come on.

1143
01:05:00,146 --> 01:05:02,731
- [Giggling]

1144
01:05:09,614 --> 01:05:11,698
- I really like your hair.

1145
01:05:11,824 --> 01:05:14,034
- [Chuckles softly]

1146
01:05:17,955 --> 01:05:20,916
You can't catch cancer.

1147
01:05:31,260 --> 01:05:35,597
- Lisa asked me
to bring her here today.

1148
01:05:38,100 --> 01:05:41,102
- Yeah, she doesn't
like my sister very much.

1149
01:05:44,607 --> 01:05:47,776
But she likes you.

1150
01:05:47,902 --> 01:05:50,153
- I like her too.

1151
01:05:58,287 --> 01:06:03,291
Her dad got her into pirates,
she said.

1152
01:06:05,753 --> 01:06:07,712
- No.

1153
01:06:07,838 --> 01:06:10,632
Lisa never knew her father.

1154
01:06:12,635 --> 01:06:14,010
- Well, I-I thought-

1155
01:06:14,136 --> 01:06:16,221
- Would you...

1156
01:06:16,347 --> 01:06:19,099
Iook in on Lisa
from time to time?

1157
01:06:27,149 --> 01:06:30,068
- Of course.

1158
01:06:55,011 --> 01:06:57,554
[Doorbell ringing]

1159
01:06:57,680 --> 01:07:00,682
[Frantic knocking]

1160
01:07:02,518 --> 01:07:04,102
Mr. Jones!

1161
01:07:06,022 --> 01:07:07,814
Mom?

1162
01:07:07,940 --> 01:07:08,898
Mom?
Dad?

1163
01:07:09,025 --> 01:07:10,442
Have you seen Mr. Jones?

1164
01:07:10,568 --> 01:07:12,152
Mom, have you seen Mr. Jones?

1165
01:07:12,278 --> 01:07:14,070
- He's gone.

1166
01:07:14,196 --> 01:07:17,073
And I can't find my car keys.

1167
01:07:17,199 --> 01:07:18,575
- Who's gone?
Mr. Jones?

1168
01:07:18,701 --> 01:07:21,619
- No, Mona.
Your dad.

1169
01:07:21,746 --> 01:07:23,747
Your dad's gone.

1170
01:07:23,873 --> 01:07:26,166
- What?
Where did he go?

1171
01:07:26,292 --> 01:07:27,250
- I don't know where.

1172
01:07:27,376 --> 01:07:29,044
I don't know where he is.

1173
01:07:33,340 --> 01:07:37,927
And I found these
behind the washing machine.

1174
01:07:38,054 --> 01:07:39,679
He's been hiding them,

1175
01:07:39,805 --> 01:07:42,557
and I don't know for how long
he's not taking them.

1176
01:07:45,061 --> 01:07:48,188
- This never would have happened
if I still lived here.

1177
01:07:48,314 --> 01:07:49,481
- Stop it!

1178
01:07:49,607 --> 01:07:52,901
You can't help him!

1179
01:07:53,027 --> 01:07:55,236
And I don't know
where he is.

1180
01:08:06,540 --> 01:08:07,957
- Dad?
- Is that your father?

1181
01:08:08,084 --> 01:08:09,292
I've been trying
to get him to move,

1182
01:08:09,418 --> 01:08:10,627
but he won't get up.

1183
01:08:10,753 --> 01:08:12,128
- Dad.

1184
01:08:12,254 --> 01:08:17,592
- The energy
is trapped in this circle,

1185
01:08:17,718 --> 01:08:19,761
and it needs to be released.

1186
01:08:23,891 --> 01:08:25,308
- Let's go home.

1187
01:08:25,434 --> 01:08:27,727
- Do you need me
to make a call for you?

1188
01:08:27,853 --> 01:08:31,106
- No, we're fine.
Thank you.

1189
01:08:34,318 --> 01:08:37,487
Why did you stop
taking your medicine?

1190
01:08:37,613 --> 01:08:40,115
- Because they're poison.

1191
01:08:40,241 --> 01:08:42,951
And they'll poison my body.

1192
01:08:43,077 --> 01:08:45,036
- No, it'll help you.

1193
01:08:49,166 --> 01:08:51,668
- You understand?

1194
01:08:51,794 --> 01:08:53,962
I have to dig right here.

1195
01:08:58,008 --> 01:09:00,468
If I don't open this...

1196
01:09:04,849 --> 01:09:07,308
I...

1197
01:09:07,434 --> 01:09:09,310
- Please...

1198
01:09:13,232 --> 01:09:15,024
Let's just go home.

1199
01:09:17,736 --> 01:09:20,071
- Don't you want me
to get better?

1200
01:09:20,197 --> 01:09:22,740
- That's all I want.

1201
01:09:36,714 --> 01:09:39,716
[Knocking]

1202
01:09:48,559 --> 01:09:51,561
[Children chattering]

1203
01:10:09,205 --> 01:10:11,080
- I have my
"numbers and materials."

1204
01:10:11,207 --> 01:10:14,334
I know it's not Friday,
but this one's special.

1205
01:10:18,088 --> 01:10:19,797
It's my dad's fake arm.

1206
01:10:19,924 --> 01:10:20,840
- Cool!

1207
01:10:20,966 --> 01:10:22,634
- It looks like a number 1,
right?

1208
01:10:22,760 --> 01:10:25,094
- Can I touch it?

1209
01:10:25,221 --> 01:10:27,263
- Pretty awesome, huh?

1210
01:10:27,389 --> 01:10:29,807
- It doesn't look like a 1.

1211
01:10:29,934 --> 01:10:30,808
It looks like an arm.

1212
01:10:30,935 --> 01:10:33,436
- It does too
look like a number 1.

1213
01:10:33,562 --> 01:10:36,940
[Children chattering]

1214
01:10:37,066 --> 01:10:39,359
- Why did your dad's arm
fall off?

1215
01:10:39,485 --> 01:10:43,154
- It didn't fall off.
It got blown off in the war.

1216
01:10:43,280 --> 01:10:44,656
Should I subtract now,
Miss Gray?

1217
01:10:44,782 --> 01:10:46,449
Miss Gray?
Miss Gray.

1218
01:10:46,575 --> 01:10:47,617
Miss Gray.

1219
01:10:47,743 --> 01:10:48,618
- What?

1220
01:10:48,744 --> 01:10:49,661
- Should I subtract now?

1221
01:10:49,787 --> 01:10:51,037
Hey, that's my dad's!

1222
01:10:51,163 --> 01:10:52,080
- Elmer!

1223
01:10:52,206 --> 01:10:54,415
- Give it back!
[Laughter]

1224
01:10:54,541 --> 01:10:56,167
- Get back here!

1225
01:10:56,293 --> 01:10:58,294
- Elmer, give Danny back
his dad's arm.

1226
01:10:58,420 --> 01:10:59,671
- Give it back right now!

1227
01:10:59,797 --> 01:11:01,589
- Elmer!

1228
01:11:01,715 --> 01:11:03,675
Hey, Elmer!

1229
01:11:03,801 --> 01:11:04,842
Give it!

1230
01:11:04,969 --> 01:11:06,010
Elmer, give it back!

1231
01:11:06,136 --> 01:11:08,554
- Give it back!

1232
01:11:08,681 --> 01:11:11,474
- Miss Gray,
you can't control the class.

1233
01:11:11,600 --> 01:11:12,976
You're gonna get fired.

1234
01:11:13,102 --> 01:11:14,811
- Shut up.

1235
01:11:14,937 --> 01:11:17,855
- No one cares about you, Lisa.

1236
01:11:17,982 --> 01:11:19,399
- Give me the arm!
- No!

1237
01:11:19,525 --> 01:11:21,359
- Help!

1238
01:11:21,485 --> 01:11:24,362
[Laughter]

1239
01:11:24,488 --> 01:11:27,365
- Miss Gray, look!

1240
01:11:27,491 --> 01:11:28,491
[Children gasp]

1241
01:11:31,203 --> 01:11:32,287
- I'm gonna divide you,

1242
01:11:32,413 --> 01:11:34,831
subtract you,
and multiply you.

1243
01:11:34,957 --> 01:11:36,791
- Lisa!

1244
01:11:36,917 --> 01:11:39,335
Go stand by the door.

1245
01:11:39,461 --> 01:11:40,503
- Ha!

1246
01:11:40,629 --> 01:11:42,839
- Ann, you need to learn
how to be nice!

1247
01:11:42,965 --> 01:11:46,009
- [Whimpering]
Oh, my God.

1248
01:11:49,638 --> 01:11:52,181
- I, uh...

1249
01:11:52,308 --> 01:11:54,684
Okay.

1250
01:11:54,810 --> 01:11:56,686
I'm sorry.

1251
01:11:56,812 --> 01:11:58,062
I...

1252
01:11:58,188 --> 01:11:59,981
[sighs]

1253
01:12:02,568 --> 01:12:03,568
[Loud thud, glass shatters]

1254
01:12:03,694 --> 01:12:05,111
[Children shouting]

1255
01:12:05,237 --> 01:12:07,155
- Lisa! Lisa!

1256
01:12:07,281 --> 01:12:08,698
Lisa. Lisa.

1257
01:12:08,824 --> 01:12:10,867
- Let me go.
- Stop it.

1258
01:12:10,993 --> 01:12:13,369
- Let me go!
- Stop!

1259
01:12:14,580 --> 01:12:16,205
- [Crying]
My mom died.

1260
01:12:16,332 --> 01:12:19,167
She died!

1261
01:12:22,671 --> 01:12:25,840
Why can't I get cancer too?

1262
01:12:29,678 --> 01:12:30,845
- I'm sorry.

1263
01:12:30,971 --> 01:12:33,222
- I'm sick of Lisa showing off.

1264
01:12:35,893 --> 01:12:36,851
- Ann!

1265
01:12:36,977 --> 01:12:39,103
- I'm gonna chop her
into pieces.

1266
01:12:39,229 --> 01:12:40,271
[Sobbing]

1267
01:12:40,397 --> 01:12:42,023
- Ann...

1268
01:12:42,149 --> 01:12:43,816
put the ax down.

1269
01:12:43,942 --> 01:12:45,276
- I'm gonna chop her!

1270
01:12:45,402 --> 01:12:46,361
- No, you're not.

1271
01:12:46,487 --> 01:12:49,155
- I'm gonna chop her
into pieces.

1272
01:12:49,281 --> 01:12:51,574
- You're not gonna chop anyone.

1273
01:12:51,700 --> 01:12:53,159
- I'm sick of her.

1274
01:12:53,285 --> 01:12:54,243
- Please?

1275
01:12:54,370 --> 01:12:56,579
- And I'm sick of you.

1276
01:12:56,705 --> 01:12:58,039
- Give me the ax.

1277
01:13:05,547 --> 01:13:09,008
There comes a moment
when you look around,

1278
01:13:09,134 --> 01:13:13,012
waiting for the person in charge
to help you,

1279
01:13:13,138 --> 01:13:18,267
and then you realize
you're the person in charge.

1280
01:13:18,394 --> 01:13:20,812
You are the grown-up.

1281
01:13:22,564 --> 01:13:25,149
You're the only grown-up there.

1282
01:13:29,154 --> 01:13:30,488
And you're not very good at it.

1283
01:13:34,243 --> 01:13:38,579
Life is much, much harder
than math.

1284
01:13:41,375 --> 01:13:42,917
Dad!

1285
01:13:57,224 --> 01:14:00,226
[Children screaming]

1286
01:14:01,270 --> 01:14:02,562
- Miss Gray!

1287
01:14:02,688 --> 01:14:05,982
[Children screaming
and shouting]

1288
01:14:06,108 --> 01:14:09,110
[Shouting fades]

1289
01:14:55,616 --> 01:14:57,658
- I got nine stitches.

1290
01:14:57,784 --> 01:14:59,660
- I got 27.

1291
01:14:59,786 --> 01:15:02,997
- 9 times 3 equals 27.

1292
01:15:03,123 --> 01:15:04,749
- You're correct.

1293
01:15:11,673 --> 01:15:14,675
[Knocking]

1294
01:15:16,386 --> 01:15:18,054
- What are you doing?

1295
01:15:18,180 --> 01:15:19,597
- I'm doing what you do.

1296
01:15:19,723 --> 01:15:22,225
[Knocking]

1297
01:15:22,351 --> 01:15:26,354
I used to imitate you at lunch.

1298
01:15:26,480 --> 01:15:29,232
The bench makes the same sound
as your desk.

1299
01:15:32,361 --> 01:15:36,280
Why do you do it?

1300
01:15:36,406 --> 01:15:39,242
- Why?
Um...

1301
01:15:40,327 --> 01:15:45,873
I do it when I feel...

1302
01:15:48,544 --> 01:15:50,336
Alone.

1303
01:15:50,462 --> 01:15:53,714
- Then that's why I do it.

1304
01:15:53,840 --> 01:15:55,633
I want to be like you.

1305
01:15:57,928 --> 01:15:59,762
- Don't do that.

1306
01:15:59,888 --> 01:16:03,808
Don't be like me.

1307
01:16:03,934 --> 01:16:06,727
- But I'm alone.

1308
01:16:09,481 --> 01:16:12,149
I'm all alone.

1309
01:16:36,967 --> 01:16:42,680
- Not only did you bring an ax
to school,

1310
01:16:42,806 --> 01:16:47,184
but you lied about having
a college degree.

1311
01:16:47,311 --> 01:16:49,770
Shame on you.

1312
01:16:54,026 --> 01:16:57,445
You're a wonderful math teacher,
Miss Gray.

1313
01:16:57,571 --> 01:17:01,240
But you are never allowed
to step foot in my school

1314
01:17:01,366 --> 01:17:03,618
ever again.

1315
01:17:24,556 --> 01:17:27,600
[Doorbell ringing]

1316
01:17:27,726 --> 01:17:30,811
- Mr. Jones!

1317
01:17:42,366 --> 01:17:43,699
Ow!

1318
01:18:01,843 --> 01:18:03,844
Hello?
[Woman shrieks]

1319
01:18:07,057 --> 01:18:10,601
- What are you doing?

1320
01:18:10,727 --> 01:18:13,521
Get out of here!

1321
01:18:13,647 --> 01:18:15,356
- You're not dead?

1322
01:18:15,482 --> 01:18:16,691
- Why would I be dead?

1323
01:18:16,817 --> 01:18:18,067
- What's going on?
- I don't know.

1324
01:18:18,193 --> 01:18:20,736
- I found your numbers
all over town,

1325
01:18:20,862 --> 01:18:22,405
and your store was left open.

1326
01:18:22,531 --> 01:18:23,698
Your car's gone-

1327
01:18:23,824 --> 01:18:25,074
- Get out of my bedroom.

1328
01:18:25,200 --> 01:18:26,575
- Who is this girl?

1329
01:18:26,702 --> 01:18:27,660
- Mona Gray.

1330
01:18:27,786 --> 01:18:29,995
- Mona Gray,
will you please get out?

1331
01:18:30,122 --> 01:18:32,331
- Should I call the police?
- No.

1332
01:18:32,457 --> 01:18:35,251
- But you need your numbers.

1333
01:18:35,377 --> 01:18:36,502
How are you gonna know

1334
01:18:36,628 --> 01:18:38,295
how you feel or who you are
without them?

1335
01:18:38,422 --> 01:18:40,965
- Andrea, I'll be right back.

1336
01:18:41,091 --> 01:18:42,091
I'm sorry.

1337
01:18:46,596 --> 01:18:50,349
- So why don't you need
your numbers anymore?

1338
01:18:50,475 --> 01:18:51,600
- Why do you care?

1339
01:18:51,727 --> 01:18:54,770
- I care because
you're the reason I love math.

1340
01:18:54,896 --> 01:18:56,605
You taught me
numbers were everything.

1341
01:18:56,732 --> 01:18:57,940
And I noticed your numbers,

1342
01:18:58,066 --> 01:18:59,775
and I used to keep
a vertical bar graph

1343
01:18:59,901 --> 01:19:02,737
measuring them
against your moods.

1344
01:19:04,406 --> 01:19:06,949
- You made a graph?

1345
01:19:11,997 --> 01:19:13,706
Would you like to sit?

1346
01:19:15,834 --> 01:19:19,545
I left the store open,
I sold my car,

1347
01:19:19,671 --> 01:19:21,547
all because of 42.

1348
01:19:23,717 --> 01:19:25,551
Who gives a damn
about anything else

1349
01:19:25,677 --> 01:19:28,679
when you're wearing a 42?

1350
01:19:28,805 --> 01:19:30,556
- I saw you that day.

1351
01:19:30,682 --> 01:19:31,974
